XSWcxtq5DV4_JYBeqKFNNA.text: We wandered upon this place while strolling by the river. We chose to sit outside to enjoy the view. The food was fantastic! I had to try the porridge, it was the best I have ever had. Others in the family tried avocado toast, fabulous, and the shakshuka, incredibly delicious as well! The coffee was perfection and the service was very pleasant. Highly recommend!

b5gz4z2SXeLLb7xvCPIMHw.text: A wonderful little spot for breakfast. Spot on flavors for food and price. Service from Zak was excellent!

REgy2EOS-W-DGcuLHq9ZbQ.text: What a beautiful little place.  We popped in here recently to grab some pastries to go, and were mesmerised by the gorgeous goodies on display. We ended up getting some incredible filo mince pies along with our croissants.   As we waited for everything to be boxed up, we got to take in the atmosphere. Beautifully decorated with plenty of floor space, Toast is an inviting spot with a delicious sounding menu. I would absolutely love to come back for a meal in the not too distant future!

UPGQelfGbOOs_XEXcK6o6w.text: Spacious, bright cafe on Shore. Great for coffee and brunch (avocado toast, pancakes, eggs Benedict). Has evening service too but not tried that. Good coffee, selection of pastries and cakes. Friendly service, reliable WiFi.
